2d:T463,Soft Red Winter (SRW) Wheat is a versatile milling wheat used in cookies, crackers, cakes, and Asian noodle production. XRT Group sources USDA Grade No. 2 SRW directly from US Gulf of Mexico and Pacific Northwest export terminals, providing reliable supply to milling and food-manufacturing buyers worldwide.

**Quality Specification**

USDA Grade No. 2: minimum 60 lbs/bushel test weight, maximum 13.5% moisture, protein typically 9–11%. Full USDA FGIS phytosanitary and grade certificate issued with each cargo.

**Logistics**

Panamax and Handymax bulk loading at USGC (New Orleans, Mobile) and PNW (Portland, Kalama). Typical transit: 18–22 days USGC to Mediterranean, 25–30 days PNW to Southeast Asia.

**Pricing**

CBOT wheat futures-basis pricing. XRT's current indicative FOB premium: +$5.00/MT. CFR/CIF destinations available with transparent freight quotes.

**Contract Terms**

GAFTA 64 (FOB) / GAFTA 49 standard. LC issuance per UCP 600. SGS quantity and quality inspection at load port.

**Typical Buyers**

Flour mills, biscuit and cracker manufacturers, noodle producers, government strategic reserves.28:["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[1200px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-12 pt-10 sm:pt-16 pb-10 sm:pb-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_400px] gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-start","children":[["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-6","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps px-3 py-1.5 border","style":{"color":"#c8973a","borderColor":"#c8973a"},"children":"AGR-001"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0]","children":"Grains & Agricultural"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-[clamp(2.25rem,6vw,4.5rem)] text-white leading-[1.0] mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","fontWeight":900,"letterSpacing":"-0.02em","textTransform":"uppercase"},"children":"SRW Wheat"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base text-[#A8A5A0] mb-8","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)","letterSpacing":"0.04em"},"children":"USDA #2 / 60 lbs/bu TW"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-base sm:text-lg text-[#C4C1BE] leading-relaxed mb-10 max-w-xl","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-archivo)"},"children":"USDA No. 2 Soft Red Winter (SRW) Wheat, 60 lbs/bu test weight, from US Gulf and Pacific Northwest terminals. CBOT Wheat benchmark at +$5.00/MT. Minimum 25,000 MT, FOB/CIF. SGS and USDA FGIS inspection. GAFTA terms."}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 border-t border-xrt-steel/15","children":[["$","div","Min. Volume",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b sm:border-b-0 sm:border-r border-xrt-steel/15 sm:px-6 sm:first:pl-0","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"label-caps text-[#A8A5A0] mb-2","children":"Min. Volume"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-black text-white","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-barlow)","letterSpacing":"-0.02em"},"children":"25,000 MT"}]]}],["$","div","Benchmark",{"className":"py-5 sm:py-6 border-b